   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CRYSTALLIZATION-STUDY OF THE GOSPEL OF GOD</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>in the Epistle to the Romans Message Eighteen The Designation of Christ s Humanity Scripture Reading: Rom 1:3-4; 8:29, 19; Heb 2:10-12; 1:6; 1 Pet 3:18 OUTLINE Christ s two natures, divine and human: Christ s human nature His humanity: According to the flesh, Christ is out of the seed of David to be the Son of Man Rom 1:3; John 3:14.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Typified by the bronze serpent Num 21:4-9.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Bearing the likeness of the serpent the likeness of the flesh of sin , without the poison of the serpent Rom 8:3b.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Related to sin, Satan, and the world 2 Cor 5:21; Heb 2:14; John 12:31.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Christ s divine nature His divinity: According to the Spirit of holiness, Christ is designated the Son of God Rom 1:4.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In power.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Out of resurrection the Triune God embodied in Christ John 11:25.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Christ s death 1 Pet 3:18: For sins, the Righteous on behalf of the unrighteous, that He might bring His believers to God.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>On the one hand, crucified in the flesh.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>On the other hand, made alive in the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>In this Spirit, Christ went and proclaimed to the fallen angels in prison probably the victory of God over Satan their leader through the incarnation of God in Christ and Christ s death in the flesh 1 Pet 3:19.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The designation of Christ s humanity Rom 1:4: Christ s humanity the flesh was not divine but human.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>In His resurrection, His humanity was designated resurrected, uplifted into His divinity, that is, into His divine glory John 12:23; Luke 24:25-26: By the Spirit of holiness.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>In the divine power.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Out of resurrection, which is the Triune God embodied in Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To be the Son of God.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>This means that He was born of God in His resurrection Acts 13:33: To be the firstborn Son of God.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Among His many brothers the many sons of God Rom 8:29.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>His redeemed believers were born regenerated with Him in the same resurrection 1 Pet 1:3; Eph 2:6a.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The two statuses of Christ s sonship: The only begotten Son of God John 1:18: Possessing the divine nature divinity.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>From eternity to eternity Psa 90:2; Rom 9:5.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>As the Second in the Divine Trinity Matt 28:19.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The firstborn Son of God Rom 8:29: Possessing both the divine nature and the human nature divinity and humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>From His resurrection through His ascension and His second coming to eternity Acts 13:33; Matt 26:64; Acts 7:55-56; Rev 1:13; Heb 1:6; John 1:51 and note 3.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>As the firstborn Son of God among the many sons of God, His many brothers Rom 8:29, 19; Heb 2:10-12.</S>
   </TEXT>
